    <h1><b></b>Frequently Asked Questions</h1>
    <p><strong>Question: Where’s the  smoking section?</strong><br />
      Answer: There’s not one. Pursuant to Mecklenburg County Ordinance,  Rural Hill is now a tobacco-free zone. This includes both smoking, smokeless  tobacco, e-cigarettes, vaporizers and other such devices.</p>
    <p> <strong>Question: Can I bring my dog or other pets.</strong><strong>&nbsp;</strong><br />
      Answer: No dogs or other pets are allowed during this event except for service  dogs. We allow dogs during the Bark in the Park which is to be held April 27th  or during the Sheep Dog Trials held the 2nd full weekend in November.</p>
    <p> <strong>Question:  Can I bring my own tent or umbrella and chair?</strong><br />
      Answer: You may bring a small umbrella for your own personal use, however the  use of large yard umbrellas and tents inside the festival area are prohibited.  You may bring a folding lawn or camp chair.</p>
    <p> <strong>Question:  Do I have to purchase tickets on line?</strong><br />
      Answer: There will be tickets for sale at the front gate. If you do not have or  have lost your ticket you will be shown where to purchase one.</p>
    <p> <strong>Question:  What is your street address?</strong><br />
      Answer: 4431 Neck Rd., Huntersville, NC 28078</p>
    <p> <strong>Question:  Can I bring in my own food?</strong><br />
      Answer: There will be vendors here to provide you with food and drink, and they  are reasonably priced. We will even have several vendors serving traditional  Scottish food.</p>
    <p> <strong>Question:  What if it rains?</strong><br />
      Answer: The Rural Hill Scottish Festival and Loch Norman Highland Games is a  rain or shine event. Activities are paused in the event of a thunderstorm and  are resumed after the threat of lightning has passed.</p>
    <p> <strong>Question: What’s with the price increase on general admission?</strong><br />
      Answer: <em>This is due to new legislation in NC requiring non-profit farms to  charge sales tax to their customers.</em></p>
    <p><strong>Question: I have a drone, can I fly it and take pictures of the  property and/or event?</strong><br />
      Drones are not allowed on Rural Hill property or at ANY  Rural Hill event unless written permission from Rural Hill Staff has been  obtained. To inquire about obtaining permission, please contact the office of  Rural Hill at 704 875 3113 or email <a href="mailto:Jeff@ruralhill.net">Jeff@ruralhill.net</a></p>
<p><strong>I still have questions- who can I ask?</strong><br />
  Just give Rural Hill staff a call at 704 875 3113. We’d love to hear from  you!</p>
